[]>narrator: The pair makes their way down a barely-trodden forest path, if this half-dead expanse can be called that. Audrey looks like made of grizzled marble under the moonlight, and Argo her jaded entourage.
[]>narrator: With sweat broken and jackets wrapped around their waists, Argo and Audrey emerge on one side of a wire fence. "now just about half an hour east from here and we have our entry point." - with those words she led the way along the fence.
[]>narrator: For about half an hour more, Argo had nothing to worry about because its phone lost all reception out here.
[]>narrator: And then, Audrey swings herself over a rusted waist-high gate, which Argo follows over much less gracefully.

[]>audrey: Well, it'll have to wait a little longer because with the heat of the sun, the stench would be fucking unbearable.

[]>narrator{target|6}: Maya hasn't been at Haley's in days, and Haley has nothing in her life keeping her together anymore. Even Audrey has Leah and Noni to hang out with and Haley is just the most insufferable piece of shit on this fucking earth, apparently. <lc> This loneliness is unbearable.<mp> The realization of it carves through the layers of meth like a scapel through flesh. Haley is alone now. She'd fucked it all up. She had something nice going on and now it's gone. She doesn't know yet what to do. When people talk about getting their head cut off or heart shot through, this is what it must feel like. The certainty that you're dead, but your body not knowing it. It's a sinking feeling, a black hole drifting its way into your soul and making its nest there. What now, Haley wonders. There's an entire coastline of possibility out there for what to do after your life got upended, and haley is quicksandsinking somewhere between not caring about any of it and wanting for the ocean to take her away from the world and herself.
[]>haley{target|1}: If you love me then why would you just abandon me??
[]>narrator: She has the feeling that if she were to lie down now, she wouldn't ever get up again-why should she? Apparently her life is so worthless and a nuisance that everyone is just spending time with her out of pity anyways. If there ever was a reason to throw your name into her crashing reachable-by-foot-river, for it to be subsumed by the rapids and swallowed by the tides once it feeds into the ocean, what would it be but this?

[]>narrator: Maya is at Roaches' again. Noise is out on a forest walk. Audrey is making new plans with Leah. Nessa is at work. Haley is doing whatever her suffering drives her to, which usually amounts of lying around in bed, underpasses, and on park benches. The recovery center is only slightly out of the way of Argo's commute, and Noni is still really fresh and fragile and generally it'd probably make a good first impression to pick her up to hang out when she literally just came here to the city and can't navigate for shit anyways, so Argo picks her up.
[]>noni: Hiiiii! :3.
[]>argo: Hi Noni.
[]>noni: Mn...
[]>noni: ...Missed you.
[]>argo: I'm also glad to see you again.
[]>noni: ...
[]>argo: So we can just walk back to my place, if that's alright with you?
[]>noni: Mhm.
[]>narrator: She does a little steppy step in place, then a little step towards Argo, who indicates with its head the direction they need to go, and then it waits for Noni to be next to it and then they share the early morning hours together, before the rising summer temperatures evaporate what little moisture dares bedew the dying trees' leaves.
[]>argo: So...
[]>argo: How's the center been treating you?
[]>noni: ...Fine.
[]>noni: Been making friends.
[]>noni: One of the girls... <ap>Riley... <ap>Really nice to Noni.
[]>argo: Crush-nice or regular-nice?
[]>noni: Hard to tell...
[]>noni: Never had many crushes.
[]>noni: Especially none that... backfired.
[]>noni: So...
[]>noni: Can't tell.
[]>noni: Weh.
[]>argo: Aw I get that.
[]>argo: I'm glad you have that place now.
[]>noni: Mhm.
[]>argo: Is the food good?
[]>noni: ...
[]>noni: There's... <ap>Group cook days.
[]>noni: That's fun.
[]>noni: They even...
[]>noni: Got Noni a bowl because she's still... scared.
[]>noni: Of...
[]>noni: Weh.
[]>argo: That's fine. Big scary world, even out here?
[]>noni: Yeah.
[]>noni: But better than...
[]>noni: ;-;
[]>argo: No worries, I get'cha.
[]>argo: Hehe.
[]>noni: ^^.
[]>narrator: The two don't make much more conversation, Noni being still an absolute mess, and Argo just kinda tired from work. It's still happy to be here though.
[]>narrator: <call:set_background(argo_apartment, 3)>When they get to Argo's place, it indicates where Noni can sit (the bed), then puts on Death Upon The Stars because it recons Noni also enjoys ambient noise, then takes off its shoes, then sits next to Noni.
[]>argo: You said you like noise?
[]>noni: Mhm! ^^.
[]>noni: ...
[]>noni: One of the... <ap>Mn... >.<
[]>noni: ...
[]>argo: Would you rather I don't ask about your past?
[]>noni: Mhm.
[]>noni: ...
[]>argo: ...
[]>narrator: The two proceed to sit in silence, room darkened by half-closed shutters, air filled with stray dust particles vibrating in the overbearing nature of noise. Noni has her eyes closed, crosslegged and gently swaying in the rhythm of ambience.
[]>noni: Noni... likes.
[]>argo: Hehe, yeah they're pretty great.
[]>argo: Saw them live a few days ago.
[]>noni: ...
[]>noni: Wanna...
[]>argo: I'll definitely invite you if I catch wind of something again.
[]>noni: ...
[]>noni: >.<
[]>narrator: Noni rubs her forehead against Argo's shoulder. Argo scritches her head, and as it continues, Noni slowly lets her head collapse against Argo's chest. Holding the frail puppy close against its overadrenalized chest, Argo leans back regardless, Noni undoubtedly listening to its racing heartbeat.
[]>noni: ...
[]>noni: You're nervous.
[]>argo: Just a bit.
[]>argo: Haven't really cuddled with someone like this in a while.
[]>noni: ...
[]>noni: Girlfriend?
[]>argo: With someone I wasn't together with, I mean.
[]>noni: ...
[]>noni: Weh.
[]>argo: Heh, it's fine.
[]>argo: You're not too much, in case you're afraid of that.
[]>noni: Am not...
[]>noni: ...
[]>argo: Good.
[]>argo: Still want me to show you my music?
[]>noni: Yes.
[]>noni: Would love to...
[]>noni: ...
[]>argo: Then lemme just...
[]>argo: Yeah, this used to be my project.
[]>noni: <3
[]>noni: Good noise.
[]>noni: Thank you for making :3.
[]>argo: Heh.
[]>argo: It's a pleasure.
[]>noni: Wa.
[]>narrator: As the two sink and drift in the ocean of blankets on Argo's bed, and the array of distorted sonic violence unfolding around them, there is intent and intimacy in their listening experience they hadn't found with many others before. If anyone, at all. Fuck. Could Nessa do this? Could...
[]>narrator: Fuck.
[]>narrator: With another hours or two of just staring at the ceiling, puppy clung to its chest, Argo has to inform Noni of the looming nature of its employment.
[]>argo: I gotta sleep soon. Because I work in the evenings and night and stuff, you know?
[]>noni: Yeah...
[]>noni: ...
[]>noni: Can Noni stay?
[]>noni: Just until.
[]>argo: ...
[]>argo: Fine.

[]>narrator: Audrey went out to the canyon today. A beautiful local rock formation, with a camping chair on top because Audrey just placed it there and then herself in it. She cracks open the first beer from the solo crate. Brain off, stare out into nature, listen to good music. Do. Not. Give. A fuck. About anything else happening in the world. []>narrator: They continue justting chat about whatever, when they're not busy feeling each other up. Whenever Nessa needily grinds against it, Argo squints and scans the entire street around them for anyone who might wanna fuck with them for being gay. Argo doesn't cling as tightly because of it.
[]>narrator: Nevertheless, the two have an hour to kill, and eventually standing up becomes too exhausting, so they collapse next to one another onto the ground, almost scissoring the way they sit, leaning into each other's shoulders, placing gentle bites, then pulling back and gazing into one another's eyes, the world around them a blur, at least when the air doesn't tense up in ways only Argo picks up, which might be paranoia or just trauma but sometimes its eyes unfocus and it has to look around and not get too comfortable embracing Nessa on the street.
[]>narrator: Time still melts away like this, and with the softness of each other's bodies, neither feels any impetus to move away from this place, even as the time is approaching and they really should get that bus.
[]>narrator: Reluctantly but knowing it's for the better (because sharing a bed is nice), they eventually get up and they're both just a little more in love with each other now, and then they're off and argo still constantly on guard, Nessa focused on just getting home, as they lead each other by the hand through the main station to the bus stop side of it, and then they're finally in and in a few minutes they'll be relieved to cuddle under sheets again.
[]>narrator{target|2}: The world has revolved another evening worth of time, as has Haley's stomach. System thrashed on alcohol and meth, she has the intuition that she still won't really forget all of the pain but maybe if she scars her soul enough, she will become such a radically different person that Maya will mercykill her or break up with her or forgive her or what ever was the point of this? <mp>Fuck Haley's life.

text_data.1750607675.816--9223372036854682739: []>narrator: The next morning, Audrey still hasn't heard from Maya so she decides to text her, as all good friends do.
text_data.1750617239.983--9223372036854681856:
[]>narrator: Maya falls to her knees as soon as the basement door is opened. Sprawled out on a grimy surgery table, Haley lays limp. Maya's tears run violently, mixing with snot and convulsions and screams into a miserable ball of grief. Roaches offers to take her hand, Maya declines.
[]>narrator: She bashes her head against the concrete surface next to her temple before she's stopped by Harsh Noise placing a hand between her head and the wall. <mp><call:show_image(raya_cuddles, 0, 300, 300)>Maya collapses into Roaches. Noise stands over them. Xelia is waiting outside.

[]>vanessa: Had a big bout of that recently.
[]>vanessa: And now do again, but that's not relevant right now.
[]>vanessa: But even in the smaller events, it sometimes feels like we grieve versions of us that existed two days ago.
[]>vanessa: And what I've learned through that is that grief is love with nowhere to go.
[]>vanessa: You have these inasnely positively charged emotions and whatever you want to receive them... can't.
[]>vanessa: And then you're stuck with them and it feels horrible.
[]>maya: ...
[]>vanessa: ...

[]>vanessa: But it's better than wallowing alone regardless of how it works, in my opinion.
[]>maya: ...
[]>vanessa: ...
[]>vanessa: You can also find a way to put your love somewhere outside of you and maybe it'll help.

[]>maya: No.

[]>vanessa: Well, as long as it helps.

[]>maya: Thank you, Nessa.

text_data.1750663134.106--9223372036854680917:
[]>narrator: Maya couldn't sleep but Xelia seems serious business, meaning she now catatonizes at home until her departure time to punctually arrive comes.There's also new cuts that appeared there some time recently. Maya can't remember when. <mp>Meeting someone new while you have fresh bandages on your arm always kinda sucks, Maya thinks. Makes for a bad first impression. The summer heat isn't helping either, so her cuts itch and fester and seep in their sodden-with-sweat gauze prison. Sucks for her.
[]>narrator:Argo stumbled out of its night shift, and the time management today is super fucked so it just insufflates a bit of speed, and then walks itself to the train station. It'll be a bit early but that just means the two can hang out for a few hours then before meeting whoever it is that as higher stakes in the body, whatever that means. Maybe Xelia started monetizing her necro operations? Though it never pegged Xelia as someone who would go down that route. Oh well, we'll see, Argo thinks.
[]>narrator: It eventually gets off the train, and heads down to Xelia's abode. As expected, it's the first individual to converge here, with Roaches and Noise presumably drifting somewhere between sleep, drug use, and air pollution.

text_data.1750663266.974--9223372036854680869:
[]>narrator: The rest of the gathering is unremarkable from the outside, nothing but a group of friends hanging out. They all know that things will just move on now. That life moves on. And that they will be ground up in history if they do not move with it in due time. Tears are shed, feelings aired in the silence between breaths, no one has anything to say.

Roaches feels everything and nothing. Nessa sees Argo's scars and hates herself. Argo doesn't matter. <mp>Haley has become a concept.
